i don\'t know how much effort building your table takes you. It does appear that there is some fuss getting everything lined up right

i built that table fairly quickly, and have it organised to make it easier to update with new info All the important stuff sits at the very beginning of a line, nowhere else. might ease the workload of building a table every turn for you.

If you prefer it your way, don\'t let me stop you.
My table is generated auto-magically from my database. I can output in Nice HTML format but it seems this forum technology doesn\'t support that.
well now, thats cheating, but it works
I\'m assuming that for the \'leave something in orbit\' just a naked decoupler doesn\'t count? (ie attach a radial decoupler with nothing attached and jettison that)

You can leave any sort of debris in orbit. PE/AP need to be above 70000. The Kerbal press will applaud the discovery of perpetual orbits and it\'s readers will marvel at how this might be useful in the future.

Oh I just noticed a mistake has snuck into things. My turn 3 craft is listed as costing 6325, which is false it should be 6550. I backtracked through the forum and e-mails and it\'s my fault; in the e-mail I listed 2x Small fuel tank as costing 225 (which is the price of 1), what should obviously have been 450.

Also, I see 35K apparently still pays more than 70, and 1400 east pays the same as orbit. I\'ve laid out before why I think sticking with the pure math is not the best decision, you probably don\'t agree which is fine and I don\'t see the need to have the same discussion again. However that said, I am brooding on some ideas of my own, would you mind if I started laying the groundwork for a second campaign? I won\'t start it just yet (I think one at a time is enough, at least until this one is underway a bit more so that the two will be in clear different stages).

Cheers

For fairness, it would add insult to injury to pay ppl different amounts for the same mission.

I think the selection of missions needs careful thought and a lot of tweaking and we can do that here. I\'ll adjust your ship cost next turn. Thx for being honest.

Yeah, that\'s fair enough.

The missions are too close together in difficulty I think. It\'s a nice idea to have a neat sequential set of objectives, but the stock parts, the thin atmosphere and the steep gravity gradient make the actual increase in difficulty from one mission to the next very small. The same will be true for the next missions you designed, especially the \'orbit, orbit with rcs, orbit while leaving anything behind, deploy powersat\'. These are all the same in difficulty really. The same for anything concerning mun orbit/return.

I think for my campaign in the future I will make missions more about delivering payloads and requiring a certain time in space, with the tech levels focussing on reducing part cost and/or increasing salvage percentage.

Anyway, turn 4 submitted!
Only two craft submitted so far. 48 hours to go!
